Package: Rvivo
Title: Rvivo Takes tumour measerements and performs data analysis.
Version: 0.9.1.0000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Christian",
           family = "Bouwens",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "c.j.bouwens@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5751-0365"))
Description: Rvivo takes two types of input: 1. Tumour measurements (height x width) or 2. pre-calculated tumour volumes in mm3. input data expects 3 columns of sample data (Cage, Treatment, mouse ID) and dates as column names. Rvivo Currently returns a .csv file with the following columns: A treatment/experiment start point, as indicated from the date the tumour size exceded a certain threshold. The tumour growth from the treatment start to the last measurement. The growth of the tumour over each measurement interval. A summation of intervals where there was growth, remission or no change (stable) in tumour size. 
